# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
var TAU = 6.283;        // ~2π
var PHI = 1.618;        // Golden ratio
var INV_SQRT2 = 0.707;  // ~1/√2

var config = {
    deflection: 4000,
    frictionCoeff: 0.004,
    approximation: 0.92,
    dispersal: 0.0003,
    streamMax: 40,
    streamDecay: 0.04,
    theta: 0.06
};

// "edges" are actually the NODES (vertices) of the graph
var edges = [
    { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// "nodes" are actually the EDGES (links/springs) connecting vertices
var nodes = [
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

var lens = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var focus = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var stream = [];
var cycle = 0;

function edgeById(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        if (edges[i].id === id) return edges[i];
    }
    return null;
}

function converge() {
    // 1) Coulomb-like repulsion between all node pairs
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < edges.length; j++) {
            var dx = edges[i].x - edges[j].x;
            var dy = edges[i].y - edges[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.deflection / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            edges[i].vx += fx;
            edges[i].vy += fy;
            edges[j].vx -= fx;
            edges[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Hooke's law spring attraction along links
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        var nodeA = edgeById(nodes[n].a);
        var nodeB = edgeById(nodes[n].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - nodes[n].rest;
        var force = (nodes[n].k || config.dispersal) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Gravity toward center (400, 300) + friction damping + position update
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        edges[i].vx += (400 - edges[i].x) * config.dispersal;
        edges[i].vy += (300 - edges[i].y) * config.dispersal;
        edges[i].vx *= config.approximation;
        edges[i].vy *= config.approximation;
        edges[i].x += edges[i].vx;
        edges[i].y += edges[i].vy;
    }
}

function emitStream() {
    if (stream.length >= config.streamMax) return;
    var source = edges[Math.floor(Math.random() * edges.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * INV_SQRT2;
    stream.push({
        x: source.x,
        y: source.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * INV_SQRT2
    });
}

function decayStream() {
    for (var i = stream.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = stream[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) stream.splice(i, 1);
    }
}

function adjustLens() {
    lens.x += (focus.x - lens.x) * config.theta;
    lens.y += (focus.y - lens.y) * config.theta;
    lens.zoom += (focus.zoom - lens.zoom) * config.theta;
}

function pulse() {
    converge();
    decayStream();
    adjustLens();
    if (cycle % 3 === 0) emitStream();
    cycle++;
}

setInterval(pulse, 16); // ~60fps
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** with a decorative particle system. Here's the breakdown:

### 🔵 Graph Physics (`converge`)
A classic force-directed graph with **6 vertices** (Hub, Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) connected by **8 spring-links**:

| Force | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Coulomb repulsion** | All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, strength 4000) |
| **Spring attraction** | Connected nodes attract via Hooke's law (each link has a rest length and stiffness `k`) |
| **Gravity** | Gentle pull toward center point (400, 300) |
| **Friction** | Velocity damped by factor 0.92 each tick |

The hub is the central, largest node connected to all others — a classic **hub-and-spoke** topology.

### ✨ Particle Stream (`emitStream` / `decayStream`)
Every 3rd tick, a **decorative particle** spawns from a random node, flies outward in a random direction, gradually slows down, and dies after 800–2000 ticks. Max 40 particles at once. This creates a subtle "emanating energy" visual effect.

### 📷 Camera/Lens (`adjustLens`)
A virtual camera smoothly interpolates (lerps at 6% per frame) toward a `focus` target — supporting smooth pan/zoom transitions. Currently the focus and lens start at the same position, so no movement occurs unless `focus` is changed externally.

### ⏱️ Main Loop
`setInterval(pulse, 16)` runs the simulation at **~60 FPS**. Each tick: physics step → particle update → camera update → maybe spawn particle.

### Notable Quirk
The variable names are **swapped** — `edges` holds the graph's **vertices** and `nodes` holds the **edges/links**. This is either intentional obfuscation or a naming mistake.

> **In summary:** This is a headless (no rendering code shown) force-directed graph engine with ambient particles and a smooth camera — likely the data/physics backend for an animated network visualization.
